		<title>Mateng Cheng | Civil / Structural Engineer</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Personal portfolio of Mateng Cheng, Civil / Structural Engineer with experience in structural analysis, finite element modeling, infrastructure resilience, and engineering documentation."
		/>
	</head>

	<body>
		<header class="site-header">
			<nav>
				<a href="#home" class="logo">Mateng Cheng</a>

				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="#about">About</a>
					<a href="#education">Education</a>
					<a href="#certifications">Certifications</a>
					<a href="/resume/" target="_blank">Resume</a>
					<a href="#projects">Projects</a>
					<a href="#experience">Experience</a>
					<a href="#skills">Skills</a>
					<a href="#contact">Contact</a>
				</div>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main id="home">
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">Civil / Structural Engineer</p>

				<h1>Civil / Structural Engineer</h1>

				<p class="hero-text">
					Ph.D. candidate in Civil Engineering with experience in structural analysis,
					finite element modeling, engineering documentation, and infrastructure resilience.
				</p>

				<div class="hero-actions">
					<a class="button primary" href="#projects">View Projects</a>
					<a class="button" href="/resume/" target="_blank">View Resume</a>
					<a class="button" href="#contact">Contact Me</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="about" class="section">
				<h2>About</h2>

				<p>
					My background combines civil and structural engineering with computational modeling
					for infrastructure applications. I have worked on structural analysis, 3D CAD modeling,
					finite element simulation, hazard mapping, and probabilistic infrastructure performance
					modeling. I am interested in Civil / Structural Engineer roles involving structural
					analysis, engineering documentation, design support, and infrastructure resilience.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section id="education" class="section">
				<h2>Education</h2>

				<div class="education-list">
					<div class="education-item">
						<div class="education-main">
							<div class="education-heading">
								<h3>Case Western Reserve University</h3>
								<span class="education-location">Cleveland, OH</span>
							</div>
							<p>Ph.D. in Civil & Environmental Engineering</p>
						</div>

						<div class="education-date">Aug 2021 – Feb 2027 (Expected)</div>
					</div>

					<div class="education-item">
						<div class="education-main">
							<div class="education-heading">
								<h3>Columbia University</h3>
								<span class="education-location">New York, NY</span>
							</div>
							<p>M.S. in Civil Engineering & Engineering Mechanics</p>
						</div>

						<div class="education-date">Sep 2018 – Feb 2021</div>
					</div>

					<div class="education-item">
						<div class="education-main">
							<div class="education-heading">
								<h3>Central South University</h3>
								<span class="education-location">Changsha, China</span>
							</div>
							<p>B.S. in Civil Engineering</p>
						</div>

						<div class="education-date">Sep 2013 – Jun 2017</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="certifications" class="section">
				<h2>Certifications</h2>

				<a
					class="certification-card certification-card-link"
					href="https://account.ncees.org/rn/2179488-1941964-aa01601"
					target="_blank"
				>
					<div class="certification-content">
						<p class="certification-type">Professional Credential</p>
						<h3>Fundamentals of Engineering (FE) Civil Exam Passed</h3>
						<p>Eligible for Engineer-in-Training (EIT) certification</p>

						<span class="certification-link">View NCEES Verification →</span>
					</div>

					<div class="certification-image-wrap">
						<img
							src="/FE.png"
							alt="NCEES FE Exam credential badge"
							class="certification-image"
						/>
					</div>
				</a>
			</section>

			<section id="projects" class="section">
				<div class="section-title">
					<div>
						<h2>Selected Projects</h2>
						<p>Engineering, modeling, and infrastructure resilience work.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="project-grid">
					<a class="project-card project-card-link" href="/projects/suspension-bridge/">
						<p class="project-type">Structural Analysis</p>
						<h3>Long-Span Suspension Bridge 3D CAD Modeling & Structural Analysis</h3>
						<p>
							Built an integrated 3D structural and terrain model for an 800 m main-span
							suspension bridge and performed SAP2000 vibration analyses under multiple
							structural scenarios.
						</p>
						<div class="tags">
							<span>SAP2000</span>
							<span>AutoCAD 3D</span>
							<span>Structural Analysis</span>
						</div>

						<span class="project-link">View Details →</span>
					</a>

					<a class="project-card project-card-link" href="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/">
						<p class="project-type">Finite Element Analysis</p>
						<h3>Finite Element Heat Conduction Analysis of a Turbine Blade</h3>
						<p>
							Developed a MATLAB Galerkin FEM solver for turbine blade heat conduction using
							linear triangular elements and validated temperature and flux results against
							ABAQUS simulations.
						</p>
						<div class="tags">
							<span>MATLAB</span>
							<span>ABAQUS</span>
							<span>FEM</span>
							<span>Heat Transfer</span>
						</div>

						<span class="project-link">View Details →</span>
					</a>

					<a class="project-card project-card-link" href="/projects/fracture-mechanics/">
						<p class="project-type">Fracture Mechanics</p>
						<h3>Fracture Mechanics FEM & XFEM-Based Crack Identification</h3>
						<p>
							Formulated an inverse crack identification workflow using fracture mechanics,
							XFEM-based crack modeling, and genetic algorithm optimization for flaw detection
							in heterogeneous materials.
						</p>
						<div class="tags">
							<span>XFEM</span>
							<span>FEM</span>
							<span>Fracture Mechanics</span>
							<span>Genetic Algorithm</span>
						</div>

						<span class="project-link">View Details →</span>
					</a>

					<a class="project-card project-card-link" href="/projects/abaqus-tension-test/">
						<p class="project-type">Finite Element Modeling</p>
						<h3>Uniaxial Tension Test & ABAQUS FEM Prediction</h3>
						<p>
							Conducted experimental uniaxial tension testing on 3D-printed PLA specimens
							and developed ABAQUS finite element models to compare experimental load-displacement
							behavior with coarse- and refined-mesh simulations.
						</p>
						<div class="tags">
							<span>ABAQUS</span>
							<span>MATLAB</span>
							<span>FEM</span>
							<span>Experimental Testing</span>
						</div>

						<span class="project-link">View Details →</span>
					</a>

					

					
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="experience" class="section">
				<h2>Industry Experience</h2>

				<div class="experience-list">
					<article class="experience-item">
						<div class="experience-heading">
							<div>
								<h3>Technician Intern – Railway Infrastructure Project</h3>
								<p>CRCC | Tianjin, China</p>
							</div>

							<span>Jul 2017 – Jun 2018</span>
						</div>

						<ul>
							<li>
								Performed structural measurements and supported construction drawing preparation
								on railway bridges and culverts.
							</li>
							<li>
								Designed reinforcement for RC beam elements and checked crack width and deflection
								against design code limits.
							</li>
							<li>
								Prepared calculations and documentation to support field execution and engineering
								review.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</article>

					<article class="experience-item">
						<div class="experience-heading">
							<div>
								<h3>Production Intern – Railway Construction</h3>
								<p>China Railway No. 5 Bureau | Dali, China</p>
							</div>

							<span>Jun 2017 – Sep 2017</span>
						</div>

						<ul>
							<li>
								Conducted field surveying and construction layout using total station and leveling
								instruments to support alignment and structural positioning.
							</li>
							<li>
								Assisted with concrete material testing, including slump and compressive strength
								specimen preparation, to support construction quality control.
							</li>
							<li>
								Supported engineers in monitoring on-site progress and resolving field-related
								technical issues.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="skills" class="section">
				<h2>Technical Skills</h2>

				<div class="skills-grid">
					<div>
						<h3>Structural / Engineering Software</h3>
						<p>SAP2000, ABAQUS, AutoCAD 3D, Mathcad</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3>Programming</h3>
						<p>Python, MATLAB</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3>Geospatial / Mapping</h3>
						<p>ArcGIS, terrain and flood raster processing, spatial dataset development</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3>Methods</h3>
						<p>
							Structural analysis, finite element modeling, Monte Carlo simulation,
							uncertainty quantification
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="contact" class="section contact">
				<h2>Contact</h2>

				<p>
					I am open to Civil / Structural Engineer opportunities involving structural analysis,
					engineering documentation, design support, and resilient infrastructure systems.
				</p>

				<p>
					Email:
					<a href="mailto:mxc1156@case.edu">mxc1156@case.edu</a>
				</p>

				<p>
					LinkedIn:
					<a href="https://linkedin.com/in/mateng-cheng-29374a293" target="_blank">
						linkedin.com/in/mateng-cheng-29374a293
					</a>
				</p>
			</section>
